<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Virtue&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/epistemology-virtue/" class="external text" title="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/epistemology-virtue/" rel="nofollow">Virtue Epistemology</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/15472a.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/15472a.htm" rel="nofollow">Virtue, a Catholic perspective</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/ptf/dhamma/sila/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/ptf/dhamma/sila/index.html" rel="nofollow">Virtue, a Buddhist perspective</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.csun.edu/~hcfll004/GkVirtue.html" class="external text" title="http://www.csun.edu/~hcfll004/GkVirtue.html" rel="nofollow">Greek Virtue</a> (quotations)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.meaningandhappiness.com/psychology-research/list-of-personal-strengths.html" class="external text" title="http://www.meaningandhappiness.com/psychology-research/list-of-personal-strengths.html" rel="nofollow">Peterson &amp; Seligman findings on virtues and strengths (landmark psychological study)</a></li>
</ul>
